political warfare against fascist Italy. The book also focuses on the relationship between the BBC Italian anti-fascist broadcasters, the British Foreign Office, and Labour Party. Key sources analysed in the book are, among others, the Foreign Office’s records, the programmes broadcast by the BBC Italian Service during the Allied campaign, the memoirs of Italian anti-fascist broadcasters, the BBC surveys on the audience and the letters sent by listeners of the Italian Service.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Radio / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAntifascism.  aAudiences.  aBBC.  aBush House.  aEuropean Resistance.  aItalian Service.  aPropaganda.  aRadio broadcasts.  aSecond World War.  aTranscripts.1 aBiundo, Ester Lo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez978311128144540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616483440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526164834423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526164834/original  a978-3-11-128144-5  Manchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packageb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles